The paper deals with the reliability and counting problems of Boolean Conjunctive Queries (CQs) over probabilistic databases, which are topics related to databases (cs.DB) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of lineage formulas, which are related to logic (cs.LO). The problem of counting the satisfying tuple subsets is a combinatorial problem, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the computation of Shapley and Banzhaf values, which are concepts from game theory and social choice theory, respectively, and are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
